The evidence with the title 'Some want earmarks back to help Congress pass bills ' says Oct 29, 2013  ... Earmarks were once used sparingly to attract votes on major bills . Beginning in the 1980s and 1990s , the use of earmarks exploded as they became a tool to garner votes for almost all bills , Frisch said. The number of earmarks in the defense spending bill alone swelled from 270 in 1996 to more than 2,500  ... 
